No, please.

1:02:05.375 --> 1:02:08.162
It will be better, I think,
if you take Diana away.

1:02:08.167 --> 1:02:09.532
I will answer any questions.

1:02:09.542 --> 1:02:11.498
We'll be downstairs if you do need us.

1:02:18.292 --> 1:02:20.578
Now I will explain why I insisted

1:02:20.583 --> 1:02:22.574
the medical examiner and his assistants

1:02:22.583 --> 1:02:25.871
wear insulated gloves
when they touch the body.

1:02:25.875 --> 1:02:27.240
Will you turn out the lights?

1:02:38.917 --> 1:02:41.283
Look closely at the neck of the victim.

1:02:46.792 --> 1:02:47.792
Lights, please.

1:02:50.458 --> 1:02:52.574
You observe those finger marks

1:02:52.583 --> 1:02:53.914
cannot be seen in the light.

1:02:53.917 --> 1:02:56.203
It is phosphorus, possibly?

1:02:56.208 --> 1:02:57.208
No.

1:03:00.333 --> 1:03:01.914
Radium x.

1:03:01.917 --> 1:03:04.408
Inflicted by the grasp of someone

1:03:04.417 --> 1:03:05.748
contaminated by the poison.

1:03:07.125 --> 1:03:08.831
Do you know such a person?

1:03:08.833 --> 1:03:09.993
Only one, he is dead.

1:03:11.167 --> 1:03:13.954
But there is a story behind all this.

1:03:13.958 --> 1:03:16.415
And I am going to ask you
to listen to some facts.

1:03:18.417 --> 1:03:19.577
= there's some curse.

1:03:19.583 --> 1:03:22.996
Diana, my dear, there are
no such things as curses.

1:03:24.250 --> 1:03:26.411
Well, they needn't look
any farther for the murderer.

1:03:26.417 --> 1:03:28.157
Here she is. - Stop it!

1:03:28.167 --> 1:03:29.532
I won't let you talk like that.

1:03:29.542 --> 1:03:32.329
If I hadn't left him, they
would all be alive today.

1:03:32.333 --> 1:03:34.699
Janos, sir Francis and Arabella.

1:03:34.708 --> 1:03:36.118
Stop it.

1:03:36.125 --> 1:03:37.331
We loved each other.

1:03:37.333 --> 1:03:38.789
We belong to each other.

1:03:38.792 --> 1:03:40.202
You never belonged to him.

1:03:40.208 --> 1:03:42.324
And no law of nature or
man can make it anything

1:03:42.333 --> 1:03:43.948
but right for us to have done what we did.

1:03:43.958 --> 1:03:47.280
He shan't reach out of his
grave and spoil our lives.

1:03:47.292 --> 1:03:48.292
I'll fight it.

1:03:49.208 --> 1:03:51.494
But what are you going to fight?

1:03:51.500 --> 1:03:53.161
Something you can't see?

1:03:53.167 --> 1:03:54.998
Something you can't reach?

1:03:55.000 --> 1:03:56.490
Something you can't touch?

1:03:59.125 --> 1:04:00.285
Oh, darling.

1:04:00.292 --> 1:04:01.292
Hold me tight.

1:04:01.958 --> 1:04:04.415
We're going to need
each other so very much.

1:04:05.500 --> 1:04:09.288
Yes, I have feared something like this

1:04:09.292 --> 1:04:11.954
ever since the day he left my laboratory.

1:04:11.958 --> 1:04:13.869
And I always doubted his death.

1:04:16.458 --> 1:04:19.074
So now you know all I have to tell you.

1:04:19.083 --> 1:04:21.165
You believe that the man who was buried

1:04:21.167 --> 1:04:23.283
as Dr. rukh was not Dr. rukh?

1:04:23.292 --> 1:04:24.828
Yes.

1:04:24.833 --> 1:04:27.074
I believe that rukh is alive and in Paris.

1:04:28.792 --> 1:04:32.614
I believe that this city
is at the mercy of a madman

1:04:32.625 --> 1:04:34.957
whose body is an engine of destruction.

1:04:34.958 --> 1:04:36.289
I talked to his mother on the telephone

1:04:36.292 --> 1:04:38.829
a little while ago, and
it is also her belief

1:04:38.833 --> 1:04:40.198
that rukh is alive.

1:04:40.208 --> 1:04:42.415
We will take immediate
steps to locate him.

1:04:43.667 --> 1:04:44.667
Gentlemen.

1:05:17.792 --> 1:05:21.705
A figure melted while a
crowd of people watched.

1:05:21.708 --> 1:05:24.415
Only one element on
earth could have done it.

1:05:24.417 --> 1:05:26.658
Diana and I were married at that church,

1:05:26.667 --> 1:05:28.373
and there were six of us in Africa.

1:05:30.125 --> 1:05:31.865
Do you suppose rukh's crazy brain

1:05:31.875 --> 1:05:33.740
drew some analogy between that fact,

1:05:33.750 --> 1:05:36.241
and the six figures of
the saints on the church?

1:05:36.250 --> 1:05:40.038
He killed two of us and
destroyed two of the six figures.

1:05:40.042 --> 1:05:41.657
= a man and a woman in each case.

1:05:41.667 --> 1:05:44.409
You and your wife must go
into seclusion immediately.

1:05:44.417 --> 1:05:48.535
Also you, Dr. benet, while we
comb Paris for this madman.

1:05:48.542 --> 1:05:51.579
It might be simpler
to get him to come here.

1:05:51.583 --> 1:05:53.164
How do you propose this?

1:05:53.167 --> 1:05:54.247
Ask him for dinner?

1:05:54.250 --> 1:05:55.365
No, not quite.

1:05:55.375 --> 1:05:56.911
But that's the general idea.

1:05:56.917 --> 1:05:58.498
Let the newspapers give out a story

1:05:58.500 --> 1:05:59.990
that the three remaining survivors

1:06:00.000 --> 1:06:02.412
of our African expedition
are leaving Paris immediately

1:06:02.417 --> 1:06:04.157
for an unknown destination.

1:06:04.167 --> 1:06:06.283
But before departing, there
will be a meeting here.

1:06:06.292 --> 1:06:08.374
What sort of meeting?

1:06:08.375 --> 1:06:10.616
Well, what do you think
would draw him, doctor?

1:06:10.625 --> 1:06:13.913
A lecture concerning
my recent experiments

1:06:13.917 --> 1:06:17.785
with radium x, and a
chance to reach you and me.

1:06:17.792 --> 1:06:20.158
You are both willing to take such risk?

1:06:20.167 --> 1:06:21.577
= of course.

1:06:21.583 --> 1:06:23.073
Yes.

1:06:23.083 --> 1:06:25.495
I will invite a limited
number of scientists,

1:06:25.500 --> 1:06:27.081
to be admitted by card only.

1:06:27.083 --> 1:06:29.699
Do you think it's fair to
expose them to the danger?

1:06:30.708 --> 1:06:33.040
There are only two
people he wants to destroy.

1:06:34.125 --> 1:06:36.912
Two, or perhaps three.

1:06:36.917 --> 1:06:38.873
My men can check the list of invitations

1:06:38.875 --> 1:06:42.163
at the gate and maybe capture him there.

1:06:42.167 --> 1:06:44.158
Also mingle with your guests.

1:06:44.167 --> 1:06:45.247
Exactly.

1:06:45.250 --> 1:06:47.741
I will set the hour of
midnight for the lecture.

1:06:47.750 --> 1:06:49.957
At that time his luminosity will be strong

1:06:49.958 --> 1:06:51.914
as he will delay taking the counteractive,

1:06:51.917 --> 1:06:54.203
hoping for a chance to use his deadliness

1:06:54.208 --> 1:06:55.618
upon Drake and me.

1:06:55.625 --> 1:06:59.243
If your men fail to
capture him at the gate,

1:07:01.417 --> 1:07:03.749
and darken the entire house.

1:07:03.750 --> 1:07:06.241
His face and hands will appear like,

1:07:06.250 --> 1:07:09.868
like phosphorus,
regardless of any disguise.

1:07:09.875 --> 1:07:13.367
And if he touches anyone?

1:07:17.458 --> 1:07:18.458
They die.

1:07:35.292 --> 1:07:37.203
- Professor lemaire.
- Professor lemaire.

1:07:37.208 --> 1:07:40.371
- Professor gothe.
- Professor gothe.

1:07:43.083 --> 1:07:45.950
- Dr. benet.
- Professor reinhardt.

1:07:49.958 --> 1:07:52.916
A very strange hour for such
a meeting, don't you think?

1:07:52.917 --> 1:07:53.952
Perhaps.

1:07:53.958 --> 1:07:56.791
But radium x is a very strange subject.

1:07:56.792 --> 1:07:59.704
Benet has his reasons.
Undoubtedly.

1:07:59.708 --> 1:08:02.120
He must have something
of importance to show us.

1:08:02.125 --> 1:08:04.241
Even the president of
our congress is here.

1:08:16.292 --> 1:08:18.624
Professor meiklejohn,
if I am not mistaken?

1:08:18.625 --> 1:08:20.081
Yes, I am meiklejohn.

1:08:20.083 --> 1:08:20.913
Who are you, sir?

1:08:20.917 --> 1:08:23.499
Jones, of the university of wales.

1:08:23.500 --> 1:08:26.457
We met once, but perhaps
you don't recall me.

1:08:26.458 --> 1:08:28.073
= t think I do.

1:08:28.083 --> 1:08:29.994
One meets so many people.

1:08:30.000 --> 1:08:32.992
I shall never forget your
treatise on radiation, sir.

1:08:33.000 --> 1:08:35.412
Oh, you remember that, huh?

1:08:35.417 --> 1:08:36.497
No doubt you are on your way

1:08:36.500 --> 1:08:38.786
to Dr. benet's demonstration.

1:08:40.833 --> 1:08:42.573
= it should indeed.

1:08:42.583 --> 1:08:45.541
I understand that no one is
to be admitted without a card.

1:08:45.542 --> 1:08:46.372
Yes.

1:08:46.375 --> 1:08:47.956
Oh, that reminds me.

1:08:49.875 --> 1:08:51.831
Yes, yes, I've got it.

1:08:51.833 --> 1:08:52.993
Forgetful sometimes.

1:08:53.000 --> 1:08:54.911
Well, under the circumstances.

1:08:54.917 --> 1:08:55.781
= of course.

1:08:55.792 --> 1:08:57.077
A nasty night.

1:08:57.083 --> 1:08:58.539
Most disagreeable indeed.

1:08:58.542 --> 1:09:00.328
I think I've caught a chill.

1:09:01.833 --> 1:09:03.323
Napoleon Brandy, sir.

1:09:03.333 --> 1:09:06.996
I believe a sip or two
would help us on our way.

1:09:07.000 --> 1:09:09.992
I suggest that we step
in here, out of the rain.

1:09:10.000 --> 1:09:11.365
I am not very much on spirits,

1:09:11.375 --> 1:09:15.448
but considering the night, why.

1:09:45.125 --> 1:09:47.207
Dr. Reno. = Dr. Reno.

1:09:47.208 --> 1:09:49.745
- Dr. Fergie.
- Dr. Fergie.

1:09:54.625 --> 1:09:58.538
- Professor meiklejohn.
- Professor meiklejohn.

1:10:11.208 --> 1:10:13.745
All are here, except one name.

1:10:13.750 --> 1:10:16.366
To be admitted instantly.

1:10:16.375 --> 1:10:19.617
Beaudine, you will stand
at the main house switch.

1:10:19.625 --> 1:10:22.947
It is to be thrown at
exactly 12:00 o'clock.

1:10:37.542 --> 1:10:39.328
No stranger has tried to come in,

1:10:39.333 --> 1:10:41.745
and all invitations are accounted for.

1:10:41.750 --> 1:10:42.910
Perhaps he won't come.

1:10:43.875 --> 1:10:44.875
He will be here.

1:10:45.833 --> 1:10:46.913
Probably he's here now.

1:10:56.417 --> 1:10:57.748
Monsieur le president.

1:10:57.750 --> 1:10:58.750
Oh, Dr. benet.

1:11:05.625 --> 1:11:08.457
If you will be patient for
just a few minutes longer,

1:11:08.458 --> 1:11:11.746
I will make final adjustments
in my laboratory and be ready.

1:12:07.250 --> 1:12:08.365
We expected you.

1:12:08.375 --> 1:12:10.115
T knew that.

1:12:10.125 --> 1:12:11.706
Five thieves.

1:12:11.708 --> 1:12:14.370
Two are gone, three are left.

1:12:14.375 --> 1:12:16.081
Do you intend to kill us all?

1:12:16.083 --> 1:12:17.083
Yes.

1:12:17.875 --> 1:12:20.366
I felt it was better to let things alone

1:12:20.375 --> 1:12:22.240
when you were first poisoned.

1:12:22.250 --> 1:12:24.081
I warned you about your brain.

1:12:24.083 --> 1:12:26.495
It began to affect my
brain almost immediately.

1:12:26.500 --> 1:12:30.413
I could feel it coming,
crawling for cells.

1:12:30.417 --> 1:12:32.203
Aren't there ever moments when you think

1:12:32.208 --> 1:12:35.200
as you used to think, when you were human?

1:12:35.208 --> 1:12:36.994
Not often now, not often.

1:12:38.500 --> 1:12:40.491
= and because of that we must die.

1:12:40.500 --> 1:12:41.990
No, because you are thieves.

1:12:42.000 --> 1:12:44.582
Five thieves, all thieves.

1:12:44.583 --> 1:12:46.619
It will be easiest just to shake hands.

1:12:47.542 --> 1:12:49.533
It will all be over in a second.

1:13:01.292 --> 1:13:02.281
My wife?

1:13:02.292 --> 1:13:05.249
In her room with Mrs.
Noyer, as you desired.

1:13:05.250 --> 1:13:06.365
But she's nervous, sir.

1:13:07.458 --> 1:13:08.914
So am I.

1:13:08.917 --> 1:13:11.203
Still, it will soon be
over, one way or the other.

1:13:11.208 --> 1:13:12.072
Yes, sir.

1:13:12.083 --> 1:13:13.744
One way or the other.

1:13:15.875 --> 1:13:17.957
I know something awful has happened.

1:13:17.958 --> 1:13:20.620
Try to compose yourself, madame.

1:13:20.625 --> 1:13:23.162
I can't stand this any longer.

1:13:23.167 --> 1:13:24.953
Find Mr. Drake and tell
him I must see him,

1:13:24.958 --> 1:13:26.448
if only for a moment.

1:13:26.458 --> 1:13:28.039
= t was ordered to remain here.

1:13:28.042 --> 1:13:29.532
Oh, please go.

1:13:29.542 --> 1:13:31.328
Oh, as you say, madame.

1:13:55.958 --> 1:13:56.993
Madame rukh.

1:13:57.000 --> 1:13:58.331
It's good of you to come.

1:13:58.333 --> 1:14:00.073
It's my duty to be here.

1:14:01.375 --> 1:14:02.831
Where is Diana?

1:14:02.833 --> 1:14:05.199
Oh, she's upstairs in her room.

1:14:44.208 --> 1:14:45.823
= Ronnie.

1:14:45.833 --> 1:14:47.494
Ronnie!

1:14:47.500 --> 1:14:48.500
= Diana.

1:14:50.250 --> 1:14:51.250
= janos!

1:15:34.125 --> 1:15:37.697
Strange Dr. benet doesn't
return, don't you think?

1:15:37.708 --> 1:15:39.323
Yes, very strange.

1:15:49.292 --> 1:15:50.748
Dr. benet?

1:15:50.750 --> 1:15:52.115
Dr. benet!

1:15:57.917 --> 1:15:58.917
He isn't here.

1:16:01.167 --> 1:16:02.167
Yes, he is.

1:16:03.500 --> 1:16:05.036
And so is rukh.

1:16:05.042 --> 1:16:06.157
Don't go any closer!

1:16:06.167 --> 1:16:07.998
Max, Louie, the front stairs.

1:16:13.667 --> 1:16:18.036
No, I can't kill you, I can't.

1:16:18.042 --> 1:16:19.327
But he must die.

1:16:23.500 --> 1:16:25.115
No, janos!

1:16:33.208 --> 1:16:34.208
Mother.

1:16:45.583 --> 1:16:46.583
No.

1:16:54.708 --> 1:16:56.448
= t must have time.

1:16:56.458 --> 1:16:58.164
I must go on to reach one more.

1:16:59.083 --> 1:17:00.664
Drake.

1:17:00.667 --> 1:17:02.498
= don't fire.

1:17:12.250 --> 1:17:13.250
My son.

1:17:15.042 --> 1:17:18.409
You have broken the first law of science.

1:17:23.167 --> 1:17:25.328
Yes, you are right.

1:17:25.333 --> 1:17:26.618
It's better this way.

1:17:33.167 --> 1:17:34.452
Goodbye, mother.

1:17:48.833 --> 1:17:49.833
Dianal

1:17:52.708 --> 1:17:53.708
Diana.

1:17:59.708 --> 1:18:01.824
My darling, you're safe.

1:18:03.458 --> 1:18:08.327
Madame rukh, permit
me to pay you my homage.

1:18:10.958 --> 1:18:12.664
Janos rukh is dead,

1:18:14.750 --> 1:18:19.540
but part of him will go on
eternally working for humanity.
